			.row
				.span12
					#ticker

			.row.about
				.span4
					%img.glyph(src="../images/glyphicons_036_file.png")
					%h3 Easy to Install
					%p Simply download a CSS file and replace the one in Bootstrap. No messing around with hex values.
				.span4
					%img.glyph(src="../images/glyphicons_341_github.png")
					%h3 Open Source
					:markdown
						Bootstrap themes are licensed under Apache 2.0 and maintained by the community on [GitHub](https://github.com/thomaspark/bootswatch).
				.span4
					%img.glyph(src="../images/glyphicons_280_settings.png")
					%h3 Tuned for 2.1.1
					:markdown
						Swatches are built for and tested with the latest version of Bootstrap. [Older versions](https://github.com/thomaspark/bootswatch/downloads) are also available for download.
				.span4
					%img.glyph(src="../images/glyphicons_023_cogwheels.png")
					%h3 Modular
					%p Changes are contained in just two LESS files, enabling modification and ensuring forward compatibility.
				.span4
					%img.glyph(src="../images/glyphicons_265_electrical_plug.png")
					%h3 Get Plugged In
					:markdown
						An <a data-toggle="modal" href="#api">API</a> is available for integrating with your platform. In use by [WPBS](http://320press.com/wpbs/), [FusionLeaf](http://www.fusionleaf.com/), [BootSnap](http://yabdab.com/stacks/snaps/bootsnap/), and others.
				.span4
					%img.glyph(src="../images/glyphicons_032_wifi_alt.png")
					%h3 Stay Updated
					:markdown
						Be notified about updates by subscribing via [RSS Feed](http://feeds.feedburner.com/bootswatch), [email](http://feedburner.google.com/fb/a/mailverify?uri=bootswatch&loc=en_US), or [Tumblr](http://news.bootswatch.com).

			.modal.hide.fade#api
				.modal-header
					%a.close(data-dismiss="modal") ×
					%h3 API
				.modal-body
					%h4 Request
					:markdown
						Send your request to `http://api.bootswatch.com`.
					%h4 Response
					:markdown
						This returns a `themes` array, and each theme has the following properties: `name`, `description`, `preview`, `thumbnail`, `css`, `cssMin`, `less`, and `lessVariables`.
					%h4 Demo
					:markdown
						A [simple example](http://jsbin.com/asowud/1/edit), using [mustache.js](https://github.com/janl/mustache.js) for templating.
					%h4 Credits
					:markdown
						Thanks to [James Taylor](http://jostylr.tumblr.com/) for [cors-lite](https://github.com/jostylr/cors-lite).
				.modal-footer
					%a.btn(href="#" data-dismiss="modal") Close

